[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of reported cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 8 112 611, with reports of cases by 217 countries and territories worldwide. The global count has now passed the 8 million case mark, having passed the 7 million case mark on 7 Jun 2020. The global case count increased by 1.6% in the past 24 hours. The USA, with more than 2.18 million confirmed cases, now represents 26.9% of the global cases of COVID-19, as other countries such as Brazil, Chile, Peru, Mexico, India, and Pakistan are reporting increased numbers of new and cumulative cases significantly. A global total of 439 051 deaths have been reported, an increase of 3874 deaths in the past 24 hours. A reminder that in the absence of well-developed contact tracing activities with testing of asymptomatic and mildly ill contacts, there is major underreporting of numbers of infections with the SARS-CoV-2 virus, possibly 1/10th to 1/20th in order of magnitude. There are also individuals who stay at home throughout their illness, sometimes, unfortunately, dying at home and who are never officially confirmed as infected with the SARS-CoV-2. These data are presented to provide relative indicators of the situations in each of the countries and comparisons between countries and regions of the world.

In descending rank order, the USA is number one for cumulative confirmed cases of COVID-19, followed by Brazil, Russia, India, the UK, Spain, Italy, Peru, Iran (having surpassed Germany in the past 24 hours) and Germany at number 10. China is number 19. In descending rank order, Brazil is number one for the number of newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours, followed by the USA, India, Russia, Mexico, Pakistan, Chile, Saudi Arabia, South Africa, and Peru.

The top 20 countries in terms of absolute cumulative cases, which include 7 from the European region, 6 from the Americas region, 5 from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 1 from the South East Asia region, and 1 from the Western Pacific region, a new country from the Eastern Mediterranean region was added in the past 24 hours. There are no countries from the Africa region. The top 20 countries with most newly confirmed cases include 7 from the Americas region, 7 from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 2 from the European region, 2 from the South-East Asia region, and 2 from the African region, none from the Western Pacific region. This listing very much reflects the "hot spots" in terms of countries with ongoing high transmission of the SARS-CoV-2 virus. - Mod.MPP]
